verses.text_plain: My son, keep my words, and lay up my commandments with thee.
verses.verse_html: 1My son, keep my words, and lay up my commandments with thee.

verses.text_plain: Keep my commandments, and live; and my law as the apple of thine eye.
verses.verse_html: 2Keep my commandments, and live; and my law as the apple of thine eye.

verses.text_plain: Bind them upon thy fingers, write them upon the table of thine heart.
verses.verse_html: 3Bind them upon thy fingers, write them upon the table of thine heart.

verses.text_plain: Say unto wisdom, Thou art my sister; and call understanding thy kinswoman:
verses.verse_html: 4Say unto wisdom, Thou art my sister; and call understanding thy kinswoman:

verses.text_plain: That they may keep thee from the strange woman, from the stranger which flattereth with her words.
verses.verse_html: 5That they may keep thee from the strange woman, from the stranger which flattereth with her words.

verses.text_plain: For at the window of my house I looked through my casement,
verses.verse_html: 6For at the window of my house I looked through my casement,

verses.text_plain: And beheld among the simple ones, I discerned among the youths, a young man void of understanding,
verses.verse_html:
7And beheld among the simple ones, I discerned among the youths, a young man void of understanding, ▼
▼ the youths: Heb. the sons

footnotes.body_html: ▼ the youths: Heb. the sons

verses.text_plain: Passing through the street near her corner; and he went the way to her house,
verses.verse_html: 8Passing through the street near her corner; and he went the way to her house,

verses.text_plain: In the twilight, in the evening, in the black and dark night:
verses.verse_html:
9In the twilight, in the evening, in the black and dark night: ▼
▼ in the evening: Heb. in the evening of days

footnotes.body_text: ▼ in the evening: Heb. in the evening of days
footnotes.body_html: ▼ in the evening: Heb. in the evening of days

verses.text_plain: And, behold, there met him a woman with the attire of an harlot, and subtil of heart.
verses.verse_html: 10And, behold, there met him a woman with the attire of an harlot, and subtil of heart.

verses.text_plain: (She is loud and stubborn; her feet abide not in her house:
verses.verse_html: 11(She is loud and stubborn; her feet abide not in her house:

verses.text_plain: Now is she without, now in the streets, and lieth in wait at every corner.)
verses.verse_html: 12Now is she without, now in the streets, and lieth in wait at every corner.)

verses.text_plain: So she caught him, and kissed him, and with an impudent face said unto him,
verses.verse_html:
13So she caught him, and kissed him, and with an impudent face said unto him, ▼
▼ with…: Heb. she strengthened her face and said

footnotes.body_text: ▼ with…: Heb. she strengthened her face and said
footnotes.body_html: ▼ with…: Heb. she strengthened her face and said

verses.text_plain: I have peace offerings with me; this day have I payed my vows.
verses.verse_html:
14I have peace offerings with me; this day have I payed my vows. ▼
▼ I have…: Heb. Peace offerings are upon me

footnotes.body_text: ▼ I have…: Heb. Peace offerings are upon me
footnotes.body_html: ▼ I have…: Heb. Peace offerings are upon me

verses.text_plain: Therefore came I forth to meet thee, diligently to seek thy face, and I have found thee.
verses.verse_html: 15Therefore came I forth to meet thee, diligently to seek thy face, and I have found thee.

verses.text_plain: I have decked my bed with coverings of tapestry, with carved works, with fine linen of Egypt.
verses.verse_html: 16I have decked my bed with coverings of tapestry, with carved works, with fine linen of Egypt.

verses.text_plain: I have perfumed my bed with myrrh, aloes, and cinnamon.
verses.verse_html: 17I have perfumed my bed with myrrh, aloes, and cinnamon.

verses.text_plain: Come, let us take our fill of love until the morning: let us solace ourselves with loves.
verses.verse_html: 18Come, let us take our fill of love until the morning: let us solace ourselves with loves.

verses.text_plain: For the goodman is not at home, he is gone a long journey:
verses.verse_html: 19For the goodman is not at home, he is gone a long journey:

verses.text_plain: He hath taken a bag of money with him, and will come home at the day appointed.
verses.verse_html:
20He hath taken a bag of money with him, and will come home at the day appointed. ▼
▼ with…: Heb. in his hand
 , ▼
▼ the day…: or, the new moon

footnotes.body_html: ▼ with…: Heb. in his hand

footnotes.body_text: ▼ the day…: or, the new moon
footnotes.body_html: ▼ the day…: or, the new moon

verses.text_plain: With her much fair speech she caused him to yield, with the flattering of her lips she forced him.
verses.verse_html: 21With her much fair speech she caused him to yield, with the flattering of her lips she forced him.

verses.text_plain: He goeth after her straightway, as an ox goeth to the slaughter, or as a fool to the correction of the stocks;
verses.verse_html:
22He goeth after her straightway, as an ox goeth to the slaughter, or as a fool to the correction of the stocks; ▼
▼ straightway: Heb. suddenly

verses.text_plain: Till a dart strike through his liver; as a bird hasteth to the snare, and knoweth not that it is for his life.
verses.verse_html: 23Till a dart strike through his liver; as a bird hasteth to the snare, and knoweth not that it is for his life.

verses.text_plain: Hearken unto me now therefore, O ye children, and attend to the words of my mouth.
verses.verse_html: 24Hearken unto me now therefore, O ye children, and attend to the words of my mouth.

tokens.text: unto me now therefore, O ye children

verses.text_plain: Let not thine heart decline to her ways, go not astray in her paths.
verses.verse_html: 25Let not thine heart decline to her ways, go not astray in her paths.

verses.text_plain: For she hath cast down many wounded: yea, many strong men have been slain by her.
verses.verse_html: 26For she hath cast down many wounded: yea, many strong men have been slain by her.

verses.text_plain: Her house is the way to hell, going down to the chambers of death.
verses.verse_html: 27Her house is the way to hell, going down to the chambers of death.
